  18 Dec 2007; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> latex-beamer-3.07.ebuild:
  Marked ~hppa (bug #195815).

  26 Oct 2007; Raúl Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org> latex-beamer-3.07.ebuild:
  Add ~alpha/~ia64 wrt #195815

  25 Oct 2007; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> latex-beamer-3.07.ebuild:
  Added ~ppc64

  14 Oct 2007; Alexis Ballier <aballier@gentoo.org>
  latex-beamer-3.07.ebuild:
  our texlive supports texmf site overlay, adapt deps to reflect that

  08 Oct 2007; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org> latex-beamer-3.07.ebuild:
  Fixed lyx-installation; bug #193381.  Make installation $ROOT-safe.

  22 Jul 2007; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org> latex-beamer-3.07.ebuild:
  Dependency and license change.

  20 Jul 2007; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org> latex-beamer-3.07.ebuild:
  Fix for emacs-support; bug #185669.

  05 Jul 2007; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org> -latex-beamer-3.00-r1.ebuild,
  -latex-beamer-3.01-r1.ebuild, -latex-beamer-3.06.ebuild,
  -latex-beamer-3.06-r1.ebuild, latex-beamer-3.07.ebuild:
  Removed old versions and keep the only version which works with teTeX-3.
  Added ~sparc-keyword as it was supported in an earlier version.

  19 Jun 2007; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org> latex-beamer-3.07.ebuild:
  Introduce doc and lyx USE-flags.  Without doc install a minimal version only.

*latex-beamer-3.07 (19 Jun 2007)

  19 Jun 2007; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org> +latex-beamer-3.07.ebuild:
  Version bump and installation change for tetex-3.

  12 Mar 2007; Alexandre Buisse <nattfodd@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Replaced text-markup by tex as maintaining herd (text-markup split).

  22 Feb 2007; Piotr Jaroszyński <peper@gentoo.org> ChangeLog:
  Transition to Manifest2.

